@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Background Image at Bottom Quarter</title>
    <style>
        /* The main page content (covering the top three-quarters) */
        .content {
            height: 75vh; /* Takes 75% of the viewport height */
            background-color: #f0f0f0; /* Optional background color for the top */
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
        }

        /* The bottom quarter with the background image */
        .bottom-background {
            height: 25vh; /* Takes 25% of the viewport height */
            background-image: url('https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRmE2-SkaYCcSht5zhpq143dBcYTeakc9zncQ&usqp=CAU');
            background-size: cover; /* Cover the container */
            background-position: center; /* Center the image */
            background-repeat: no-repeat; /* Prevent repetition */
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="content">
        <p1>
           
            Last Updated: 23/07/2024
            <br />
            The Bumblebee Foundation ("we," "our," "us") values your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal information.<br />
            This policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your data when you engage with us.
            <br />
            1. Information We Collect
            <br />
            We may gather:
            <br />
            Personal Information: Such as your name, email, phone number, and address.
            Financial Information: Securely processed payment details for donations.
            Usage Data: Non-personal details like your IP address, browser type, and site usage.
            Cookies: Used to enhance your experience on our website.
            <br />
            2. How We Use Your Information
            We use your data to:
            <br />
            Process donations and provide receipts.
            Communicate about our initiatives and events.
            Improve our website and services.
            Comply with legal requirements.
            <br />
            3. Sharing Your Information
            We do not sell or trade your data. It may be shared with trusted service providers (e.g., payment processors) or as required by law.
            <br />
            4. Data Security
            <br />
            We use appropriate measures to protect your data, though no method is completely secure.
        </p1>
    </div>
    <div class="bottom-background"></div>
</body>
</html>

